The All Progressives Congress (APC) in Niger State has expressed its willingness to work with the opposition parties to develop the state. Speaking with journalists shortly after the declaration of Abubakar Sani Bello as winner of the election, the state chairman of APC, Engineer Jibril Imam promised that the incoming administration would form an all inclusive government. “We will work with the opposition to move the state forward. This is no longer about the party but about the state and its development,” he noted. He appreciated all the opponents who stepped down and backed the Governor in his re-election bid, saying the administration would work with them to transform the state. Defection report part of PDP propaganda — Niger APC What new alliances, shifting bases mean in Niger State Bayelsa governorship: APC, PDP in a battle of shark and ocean